<HEADLINE>
FT  11 SEP 92 / More time for Collor's defence
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINA LAMB
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRASLIA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PRESIDENT Fernando Collor of Brazil last night was granted an extra week to
prepare his defence to the Congressional commission considering whether he
should be impeached for corruption, Christina Lamb reports from Braslia.
The Supreme Court ruled that Mr Collor will have until September 22, instead
of next Tuesday as was scheduled.
Mr Collor's aides greeted the decision as his first victory in the
impeachment battle.
The delay may mean that no Congressional vote on impeachment would occur
until after the municipal elections to be held on October 3. Presidential
advisers believe that would increase his chances of survival.
Earlier yesterday, though, Mr Jorge Bornhausen, Mr Collor's political
co-ordinator, resigned. He was angered by Mr Collor's refusal to include his
suggestions in a speech to the nation 10 days ago.
