FT  10 SEP 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool is selling well at firm prices. Demand from Japan and the
EEC is good, and China is also said to be behind some of the Japanese
buying. The Australian Wool Corporation's market indicator has maintained
last week's small gain and is unchanged at 545c/kg. There was almost a
complete clearance at Wednesday's Newcastle sale, a mere 2 per cent was
passed in at Adelaide, and 10pc at Fremantle. Erratic fluctuations in the US
and Australian dollars keep prices changing even where wool itself is
selling well. The trade believes they undermine confidence, and add to
recessionary pressures.
