FT  10 SEP 92 / Civil servants accept pay deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SMITH, Labour Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MEMBERS of three Civil Service unions have accepted offers that will lead to
salary rises of between 4 per cent and 4.5 per cent and a significant
extension of performance pay.
The decisions by the IRSF tax union, the IPMS specialists union and the FDA
top civil servants' association mean that only one Civil Service union has
yet to settle this year.
Most members of the NUCPS accepted the advice of their leaders to accept the
pay offer, but reject plans for performance-related pay and devolving pay
bargaining to departments.
The Treasury subsequently withdrew the offer. Talks with the union are
continuing on what will happen next. Senior members of the union, who are
covered by a separate arrangement, have voted for acceptance.
The decisions by the IPMS, FDA and IRSF were all carried by overwhelming
majorities.
