<HEADLINE>
FT  10 SEP 92 / Shares fall in building companies
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR, Construction Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH construction and building material shares fell steeply again
yesterday as bad news continued to pour out of the housebuilding sector.
The share price of English China Clays, the world's largest producer of
china clay, dropped almost a sixth to 371p after the company announced an
unexpected Pounds 11m provision against its UK housebuilding division.
Taylor Woodrow's share price, which had fallen by almost two-thirds since
May, fell a further 18 per cent to 35p after the company announced it had
made a Pounds 16m first-half pre-tax loss.
On Tuesday, Wimpey, Britain's second largest housebuilder, announced it was
halving its interim dividend.
