<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 92 / International Company News: TWA cuts jobs and services
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TRANS World Airlines, the US carrier operating under the protection of
Chapter 11 of the US bankruptcy code, said it has set a winter schedule
effective from October 25 under which it will eliminate service to 12
cities, Reuter reports from New York.
The workforce will be cut by up to 10 per cent as a result of the changes.
The carrier said it will stop flying to Istanbul, Moscow, Copenhagen and
Stockholm and to eight US cities.
TWA said the 'reallocation' of its resources, coupled with implementation of
agreements calling for a 15 per cent wage and benefit cut and work-rule
concessions by all US employees in exchange for a 45 per cent equity stake
in the airline, would result in a 'revitalised' TWA.
</TEXT>
