<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 92 / International Company News: Federal Mogul to seal TRW deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DETROIT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FEDERAL Mogul, the US vehicle components manufacturer, says that it is to
pay Dollars 213m to acquire the automotive aftermarket business of TRW, the
US technology group.
Federal Mogul also plans to take a Dollars 14m charge in the fourth quarter
of 1992 to cover job cuts, relocations and asset disposals connected with
the deal, Reuter reports from Detroit.
Federal Mogul, which announced the acquisition on August 23, disclosed the
information in a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
Federal Mogul also said that it estimated that total expenses for the
rationalisation of the purchase would reach about Dollars 28m.
The remaining Dollars 14m which was not taken in the fourth quarter charge
would be capitalised, the company declared.
The expenses relate to the costs of eliminating duplication between the two
companies' aftermarket parts operations in the areas of personnel,
warehousing, information management, shipping, marketing and administration.
Federal Mogul also said it believed that by eliminating such duplication it
could achieve cost savings of about Dollars 21m a year during and after
1995, with about 95 per cent of that figure realised during 1994.
The deal for the TRW aftermarket parts distribution business, which has
annual sales of more than Dollars 300m, also includes a long-term supply and
trademark agreement.
That agreement makes Federal Mogul the exclusive supplier of TRW-brand
engine and chassis parts to the independent automotive aftermarket business.
The transaction is expected to close by the end of October.
Federal Mogul said it would finance the acquisition with a combination of
equity and bank debt but the company had not determined the amount of each.
Chemical Banking had agreed to provide senior bank financing under a term
loan, Federal Mogul said.
</TEXT>
