</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MERRILL Lynch, the US brokerage, has obtained permission from the Korean
ministry of finance to upgrade its Seoul representative office into a full
branch, the sixth overseas securities house to do so, Reuter reports. The
branch will provide Won10bn (USDollars 12m) in operating funds, allowing
Merrill Lynch to engage only in broking.
